---
config:
  theme: redux-dark-color
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor user
    participant front as Frontend
    participant auth as UserAuth
    participant recipe as RecipeCatalog
    participant menu as MenuShuffle
    participant nutri as Nutrition
    participant ai as ImageProcessing
    participant aimodel as AIModel
    participant notif as Notifications
    participant kafka as Kafka
    participant db as PostgreSQL
    participant mongo as MongoDB
    participant apinutri as NutritionAPI

    rect rgb(30, 30, 60)
        Note over user,mongo: CUJ 1 — Login and load home screen
        user->>front: login
        front->>auth: POST /auth/v1/login
        auth->>db: SELECT user WHERE email = ?
        db-->>auth: user row
        auth-->>front: { access_token, refresh_token, user }

        par Load in parallel (frontend fires both at once)
            front->>recipe: GET /recipe-catalog/v1/recipes
            recipe->>mongo: find recipes by user_id
            mongo-->>recipe: recipe documents
            recipe-->>front: recipes[]
        and
            front->>menu: GET /menu/v1/active
            menu->>mongo: find active menu by user_id
            mongo-->>menu: menu or null
            menu-->>front: menu (if exists)
        end
    end

    rect rgb(30, 60, 30)
        Note over user,apinutri: CUJ 2 — Create recipe manually + calculate nutrition
        user->>front: fill recipe form, submit
        front->>recipe: POST /recipe-catalog/v1/recipes
        recipe->>nutri: POST /nutrition/v1/calculate (sync HTTP)
        nutri->>apinutri: lookup unknown ingredients
        apinutri-->>nutri: nutrient data
        nutri-->>recipe: macros_per_serving
        recipe->>mongo: save recipe with macros
        mongo-->>recipe: saved recipe
        recipe-->>front: 201 { recipe with macros }
        recipe->>kafka: recipe.created (async, for menu recalc etc.)
    end

    rect rgb(60, 30, 30)
        Note over user,apinutri: CUJ 3 — Upload image + process + calculate nutrition
        user->>front: upload photo of recipe
        front->>recipe: POST /recipe-catalog/v1/recipes/upload
        recipe-->>front: 202 Accepted { upload_id } (don't make user wait)
        recipe->>kafka: recipe.image.uploaded { upload_id, image_url, user_id }

        kafka->>ai: consume recipe.image.uploaded
        ai->>aimodel: send image for transcription
        aimodel-->>ai: extracted recipe text
        ai->>nutri: POST /nutrition/v1/calculate
        nutri->>apinutri: lookup ingredients
        apinutri-->>nutri: nutrient data
        nutri-->>ai: macros
        ai->>mongo: save completed recipe with macros
        ai->>kafka: recipe.transcription.completed { user_id, recipe_id }
        kafka->>notif: consume recipe.transcription.completed
        notif-->>user: push/email "Your recipe is ready!"
    end

    rect rgb(40, 40, 80)
        Note over user,mongo: CUJ 4 — Generate a menu (MVP shuffle)
        user->>front: set time range + meals per day, hit generate
        front->>menu: POST /menu/v1/generate
        Note right of front: {<br/> time_range: "week",<br/> meals_per_day: 3,<br/> strategy: "shuffle"<br/>}

        menu->>recipe: GET /recipe-catalog/v1/recipes (user's full catalog)
        recipe-->>menu: recipes[] with macros

        Note over menu: shuffle algorithm runs here,<br/>picks recipes to fill slots,<br/>calculates total macros for the period

        menu->>mongo: save menu as DRAFT
        mongo-->>menu: saved menu { id, status: draft }
        menu-->>front: 200 { menu with daily breakdown + total macros }

        user->>front: review menu, confirm it
        front->>menu: PATCH /menu/v1/{id}/confirm
        menu->>mongo: update status draft → active, archive previous active
        mongo-->>menu: updated menu
        menu-->>front: 200 { active menu }
        menu->>kafka: menu.activated { user_id, menu_id }
    end

    rect rgb(40, 80, 40)
        Note over user,mongo: CUJ 4b — Future: constrained generation
        user->>front: set constraints<br/>(craved recipes, calories, ease, time)
        front->>menu: POST /menu/v1/generate
        Note right of front: {<br/> time_range: "week",<br/> meals_per_day: 3,<br/> strategy: "constrained",<br/> pinned_recipes: ["id1","id2"],<br/> targets: { calories: 2000 },<br/> filters: { max_prep_minutes: 30 }<br/>}
        Note over menu: same endpoint, same service,<br/>strategy field picks the algorithm.<br/>pinned slots are filled first,<br/>algorithm fills the rest.
        menu->>recipe: GET /recipe-catalog/v1/recipes
        recipe-->>menu: recipes[]
        menu->>mongo: save as DRAFT
        menu-->>front: menu with breakdown
    end